  "_note_v2": "Expanded from 5 to 10 personas for v2 sweep. Added: young_mom, working_woman, premium_occasion, office_gifter, visiting_relative. Three new behavioral flags introduced: responds_to_power_wall (L4 effect target), impulse_prone (L4 impulse-fixture target), high_value (basket-value multiplier).",
  "notes_on_chi_square": "Each arrival/dwell distribution is sampled as `chi2(df) * scale + shift`, then clipped to [min, max] with resampling on overflow.",
  "qualitative_check": {
    "morning_peak_11am_1pm": "mission_mom + young_mom + office_gifter + browser tail",
    "lunch_dip_2pm_4pm": "tails only",
    "evening_peak_5pm_9pm": "family_weekend + young_woman + working_woman + premium_occasion + quick_trip_male + visiting_relative",
    "late_evening_9pm_10pm": "tail of family_weekend + quick_trip_male"
  },
  "_note_v3": "Added price_elasticity per persona (0=inelastic, 1=very sensitive). Engine rejects expensive items probabilistically based on agent's elasticity \u00d7 (item_price/typical).",
  "_note_v3_1": "v3.1 recalibration: bumped intent_strength and queue_tolerance to match real Diwali Saturday shopper behavior (festive day = more decided, more patient). Browser intent slightly raised (0.10\u21920.18) \u2014 Mahabachat pulls some browsers into conversion.",
  "_note_v3_2": "v3.2: bumped queue tolerance significantly. Festive shoppers who came with a basket will wait 40-70 min before abandoning. Only the time-constrained personas (working_woman, quick_trip_male, browser) abandon under 20 min."
}